---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="IntraAlpha — Lucas Sommer" description="Options-only trading platform with proprietary screeners, historical option data, real-time charting, and algorithmic trading. Built for probability-based options traders.">

  <article class="project-detail container">

    <a href="/projects" class="back-link">&larr; All Projects</a>

    <div class="project-hero">
      <div class="project-icon-lg" style="background:rgba(219,39,119,0.12); color:#f472b6;">IA</div>
      <div>
        <h1>IntraAlpha</h1>
        <span class="project-status status-exploring">Transitioning</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="project-lede">
      The world's best options-only platform. Price efficiency, research, and probability-based trading — giving retail traders institutional-level data access for options and equities.
    </p>

    <div class="project-tags-lg">
      <span class="tag">Options</span>
      <span class="tag">Algo Trading</span>
      <span class="tag">Finance</span>
      <span class="tag">Discord</span>
      <span class="tag">intraalpha.com</span>
    </div>

    <div class="detail-grid">

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>What is IntraAlpha?</h2>
        <p>IntraAlpha combines data from OPRA and US exchanges to give retail traders the same level of data access as institutions. The platform offers proprietary options tools, real-time charting, algorithmic trading, and a daily research report — all focused on options.</p>
        <p>It started as a full trading platform with subscriptions, tools, and resources, then grew into a Discord-based community of traders. The platform runs on Google Cloud and pulls financial data from industry leaders ThetaData and Polygon, with charting powered by TradingView.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Platform Tools</h2>
        <div class="tools-grid">
          <div class="tool-card">
            <h3>Options Screener</h3>
            <p>Customizable tool that identifies profitable trade setups. Filter by percent away from ATM strike, efficiency percent, market cap, stock price, directional bias, and weeks until expiration.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tool-card">
            <h3>Historical Option Graph</h3>
            <p>See how expired options performed in the past. Millions of contracts across hundreds of equities and ETFs with option data going back up to 7 years. OHLCV in 5-minute intervals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tool-card">
            <h3>Best Options Report</h3>
            <p>Daily automated analysis of 400+ widely-traded stocks with weekly options. Identifies potential profitable strategies each morning before market open.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tool-card">
            <h3>IV Analysis Tools</h3>
            <p>Proprietary tools for historical implied volatility, IV curves across expiration dates, and IV curves across strike prices. Use IV to your advantage by understanding its impact on option prices.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tool-card">
            <h3>Option Charts</h3>
            <p>Industry-leading charting powered by TradingView. Real-time data, responsive and mobile-friendly. Plot options data with the same tools institutions use.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tool-card">
            <h3>Algo Trading</h3>
            <p>Trade equities algorithmically for free via Alpaca. Submit options orders via API using IBKR's Trader Workstation. Real-time audio alerts for US equities.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Best Options Report — Results</h2>
        <p>The Best Options Report runs a comprehensive daily review of over 400 stocks. Key findings from the tracked results:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Short puts were the top performer</strong> — representing 60% of profits generated</li>
          <li><strong>Short calls generated $136,518 in premium</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Short puts delivered $86,703 in premium</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Long calls and long puts were losers</strong> across all variables — confirming the selling premium thesis</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The data reinforces what experienced options traders already know: selling premium consistently outperforms buying it. IntraAlpha's tools are built around this probability-based approach.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Data & Infrastructure</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>100% market coverage</strong> — real-time, 15-minute delayed, and 24-hour delayed data packages</li>
          <li><strong>ThetaData + Polygon</strong> — financial data from industry leaders</li>
          <li><strong>TradingView</strong> — charting technology</li>
          <li><strong>Google Cloud</strong> — infrastructure</li>
          <li><strong>Alpaca</strong> — commission-free algorithmic equity trading</li>
          <li><strong>IBKR TWS</strong> — options order submission via API</li>
          <li><strong>tastytrade partnership</strong> — open and fund a tastytrade account through IntraAlpha, receive a year of IntraAlpha Premium free</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Community & Content</h2>
        <p>IntraAlpha has a growing community of options traders sharing ideas and building followings as contributors. The ecosystem includes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Discord community</strong> — real-time trade discussion and algo signals</li>
          <li><strong>Best Options Report newsletter</strong> — daily pre-market analysis</li>
          <li><strong>Educational courses</strong> — including "The Complete Guide to Option Selling: From Basics to Advanced Strategies"</li>
          <li><strong>Product guides</strong> — how to use the screener, historical graph, and other tools</li>
          <li><strong>X / Twitter</strong> — market commentary and platform updates</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Current Direction</h2>
        <p>IntraAlpha is transitioning from a full subscription SaaS platform to a leaner model:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Simplifying</strong> — streamlining the tool set, cutting infrastructure costs</li>
          <li><strong>Discord-first</strong> — centering the community and algo signals on Discord</li>
          <li><strong>Algo migration</strong> — moving the core algorithm to Alpaca for equities</li>
          <li><strong>Lessons learned</strong> — the algo works, but the business model needed to be leaner. Productizing knowledge is different from building sustainable infrastructure</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="email-capture">
      <h3>Follow IntraAlpha</h3>
      <p class="capture-sub">Get updates on the algo, the Discord community, and where IntraAlpha is headed next.</p>
      <form class="email-form">
        <input type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required />
        <button type="submit">Subscribe</button>
      </form>
    </div>

    <!-- Related Projects -->
    <div class="related-projects">
      <h2>Related Projects</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/projects/onit" class="related-card">
          <div class="related-icon" style="background:var(--status-building-bg); color:var(--status-building-text);">On</div>
          <div><div class="related-name">Onit</div><div class="related-desc">AI-powered marketing — another platform play</div></div>
        </a>
        <a href="/projects/monkey-business" class="related-card">
          <div class="related-icon" style="background:var(--surface-2); font-size:1.2rem;">&#x1F412;</div>
          <div><div class="related-name">Monkey Business</div><div class="related-desc">The mindset behind trading, risk, and entrepreneurship</div></div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </article>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  @import '../../styles/project-detail.css';

  .tools-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .tool-card {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .tool-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
  }

  .tool-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .tool-card p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .tools-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
